Conclusions
Adapt object recognition models, i.e. neural networks pre-trained on image classifaction, to visual search tasks, using transfer learning methods from machine learning. For details, please see:
https://github.com/NickleDave/visual-search-nets
Object recognition models similarly rank impact of target-distractor pairs on accuracy
• Biases learned from natural images cause models to "behave" like humans performing visual search
• Closer analysis and visual explanation techniques suggest neural network models map pixels to output, do not represent target as humans might do
• In spite of this, these models may predict target-distractor discriminability in humans
◦ similar to ideal observer models
